    // The change in profit for a window [i, i + k -1] is:
    // (sum of 0 * prices[i..i+halfK-1] - sum of original strategy[i..i+halfK-1] * prices[i..i+halfK-1]) 
    // + (sum of 1 * prices[i+halfK..i+k-1] - sum of original strategy[i+halfK..i+k-1] * prices[i+halfK..i+k-1])
    // Which simplifies to:
    // -sum of original strategy[i..i+halfK-1] * prices[i..i+halfK-1] 
    // + sum of prices[i+halfK..i+k-1] - sum of original strategy[i+halfK..i+k-1] * prices[i+halfK..i+k-1]

    // To optimize, precompute the sum of prices and the sum of strategy[i] * prices[i] for all possible windows

    // Compute the difference array where diff[i] is the profit change if window starts at i
    // We can use sliding window to compute the sum of prices and strategy * prices for the two halves

    if (k > n) {
        return originalProfit; // cannot perform any modification
    }

